60|$|I {{smoke in}} bed until I {{have to go}} to sleep; <b>I</b> <b>wake</b> <b>up</b> <b>in</b> <b>the</b> night, {{sometimes}} once, sometimes twice; sometimes three times, and I never waste any of these opportunities to smoke. This habit is so old and dear and precious to me that I would feel as you, sir, would feel if you should lose the only moral you've got--meaning the chairman--if you've got one: I am making no charges: I will grant, here, that I have stopped smoking now and then, for a few months at a time, but it was not on principle, it was only to show off; it was to pulverize those critics who said I was a slave to my habits and couldn't break my bonds.|$|E
